- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper deals with natural language processing and text analysis. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper proposes a method for embedding legal text into a continuous vector space. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is relevant as the paper uses machine learning techniques to analyze legal text and draw insights. 
- cs.CY (Computers and Society) is relevant as the paper deals with analyzing policy differences across government branches. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is also relevant as the paper deals with analyzing relationships between different word sources based on their texts.
